translated: Forshufvud, Sten Gabriel Bernhard, dentist, Gothenburg, born February 9, 1903 in Ramsele, Västernorrland. First marriage in 1925 to Karin Thorsell. Children: Gull, born in 1926, Ragnar, born in 1931, Gunnar, born in 1945. He received his high school degree in Uddevalla in 1921, completed his dental studies in 1922 and obtained a dental degree in 1924. He later received a degree in Chirurgien Dentiste de TUniversité de Bordeaux in 1934. He defended his thesis in medicine at Lund University in 1941. He practiced dentistry in Gothenburg and wrote several papers, including "Något om orsakerna t. den s. k. symmetriska extraktionens kariesprofylaktiska verkan" (33), "L’effet de régimes carencés etc." (35), "Kan variation o. oregelbundenhet etc. vara orsak t. tandkaries?" (36), "Tandkaries etc. h. vilda svin" (38), "La carie dentaire chez le rat etc." (38), "über Zahnischmielitz etc." (graduation thesis in 1941), "über die Nutrition der harten Zalingewebe" (43), "A Study of the Paracapillary Nutrition Canals etc." (46), and "Tändernas hälsovård" (46).
